<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-24T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/933: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Consul General at Capetown</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Linnell</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-24T20:00:00-04:00">January 24,
                                1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>12. Reference your 24, January 18, 5 p.m. Treasury asks that Financial
                        Secretary be informed that no monetary conference has as yet been scheduled.
                        Part of the Russian delegation of experts has arrived for informal technical
                        discussions of the same bilateral and preliminary character as those
                        previously held with the technical experts of other United Nations including
                        the Union. You will be promptly informed of any decision to hold a formal
                        conference.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>